    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan across all 4 files in 7 precise steps:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add Model Rename to Ollama\n\n### What was found\n\nAll required infrastructure already exists — no new imports needed in any file. The `RenameHandler` can directly reuse `CopyModel`, `manifest.ParseNamedManifest`, `model.ParseName`, and `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg` which are all already imported in `server/routes.go`.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `api/types.go`: Add `RenameRequest`\nInsert after `CopyRequest` (~line 765):\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2 — `api/client.go`: Add `Client.Rename()`\nInsert after `Client.Copy()` (~line 387) — identical pattern, POST to `/api/rename`, returns `error`:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    return c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — `server/routes.go`: Add `Server.RenameHandler()`\nFull logic after `CopyHandler` (~line 1483):\n1. Bind JSON → `api.RenameRequest`\n2. Validate non-empty source/destination → 400\n3. `model.ParseName()` + `.IsValid()` → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if no error, destination exists → **409 Conflict**\n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — `os.ErrNotExist` → **404**, other errors → 500\n6. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` — failures → 500 with \"rename partially succeeded (copy done)\" message\n7. Success → **200** `{\"status\": \"success\"}`\n\n### Step 4 — `server/routes.go`: Register route in `GenerateRoutes()`\nAdd immediately after `r.POST(\"/api/copy\", s.CopyHandler)`:\n```go\nr.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)\n```\n\n### Step 5 — `cmd/cmd.go`: Add `RenameHandler` function\nAfter `CopyHandler` (~line 1350), follows the exact same pattern — `ClientFromEnvironment`, build `api.RenameRequest`, call `client.Rename()`, print `Renamed \"src\" to \"dst\"`:\n```go\nfunc RenameHandler(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error { ... }\n```\n\n### Step 6 — `cmd/cmd.go`: Add `renameCmd`\nAfter `copyCmd` definition:\n```go\nrenameCmd := &cobra.Command{\n    Use:     \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\",\n    Short:   \"Rename a model\",\n    Args:    cobra.ExactArgs(2),\n    PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat,\n    RunE:    RenameHandler,\n}\n```\n\n### Step 7 — `cmd/cmd.go`: Wire into `rootCmd.AddCommand()`\nInsert `renameCmd` between `copyCmd` and `deleteCmd` in the existing `AddCommand(...)` call.\n\n---\n\nNo new imports are required in any file. Zero existing code is modified — only additions.",
